name: Air Canada New Livery 777-300ER Landing and Takeoff at Calgary Airport
description:
Air Canada's new paint on the 77W looks better and better every time I see it! Here we have the first and oldest 77W in AC's fleet arriving and departing Calgary International Airport on a one-off equipment swap from and to AC's largest hub, Toronto-Pearson. ATC is included, hope you enjoy this masked 77W!

Thanks for watching!

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: Air Canada (ACA/AC)
Aircraft: Boeing 777-333/ER (B77W)
Flight Number: AC149/AC154
Aircraft Name: 731 
Livery: New (2017)
Engines: 2x GE90-115B
Registration: C-FITL
Route: Toronto-Pearson (YYZ) - Calgary (YYC) - Toronto-Pearson (YYZ)
Callsign: AIR CANADA 149/154 heavy 
Runway used: 17L, 17R
Date filmed: July 15, 2018
